Package org.sat4j.tools.counting

Interface IModelCounter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractApproxMC, ApproxMC, ApproxMC2, ModelCounterAdapter
    public interface IModelCounter
    This interface defines how to count the models of a formula.
    Author:
    Romain Wallon

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      BigInteger countModels()
      Computes the number of models of the underlying formula.
      void reset()
      Resets this counter.

    • Method Detail

      • countModels

        BigInteger countModels()
        Computes the number of models of the underlying formula.
        Returns:
        The number of models of the formula.

      • reset

        void reset()
        Resets this counter. This method only makes sure that counting again the models will return the same results. In particular, none of the original constraints are removed.
